cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.MA 

This paper deals with reinforcement learning, specifically off-policy temporal-difference learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of generalized Bellman equations, which is a common topic in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the use of Markov chain theory, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
